The lesson will cover the fundamental concepts of analog inputs, ADC operation, and the challenges associated with analog signal processing. Students will learn how to implement calibration and scaling techniques to improve measurement accuracy and design practical applications utilizing analog inputs in Arduino projects. By the end of the lesson, students will have a comprehensive understanding of how to leverage analog inputs to innovate and create solutions in embedded systems.

