        \item $-\cos(x) + C$
        \item $\tan(x) + C$
        \item $-\sin(x) + C$
    \end{enumerate}

    \item What is the area under the curve of $f(x) = x^2$ from $x=0$ to $x=1$?
    \begin{enumerate}
        \item $\frac{1}{2}$
        \item $\frac{1}{3}$
        \item $\frac{2}{3}$
        \item $1$
    \end{enumerate}

    \item Why do we include a constant of integration in indefinite integrals?
    \begin{enumerate}
        \item It simplifies calculations.
        \item It accounts for all possible antiderivatives.
        \item It makes the function continuous.
        \item It is required for definite integrals.
    \end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}

