\section*{Summary}
In this lesson, we introduced the concept of integration, focusing on antiderivatives and indefinite integrals. We explored basic integration techniques, such as the power rule, and discussed the importance of the constant of integration. We also examined how integration is used to calculate areas under curves and solved various examples, including initial value problems and definite integrals. Integration is a powerful tool in mathematics and engineering, providing solutions to problems involving accumulation and area. Understanding these concepts is crucial for further studies in calculus and its applications.

